Python has a set of built-in methods that you can use on strings.

> Upper Case :
a = "Hello, World!"
print(a.upper()) # HELLO WORLD

> Lower Case :
a = "Hello, World!"
print(a.lower()) # hello world

> Remove Whitespace :
a = " Hello, World! "
print(a.strip()) # returns "Hello, World!"

> Replace String :
a = "Hello, World!"
print(a.replace("H", "J"))

> Split String :
a = "Hello, World!"
print(a.split(",")) # returns ['Hello', ' World!']
